15:07.406 --> 15:08.616
I'm sorry, Casey.

15:08.699 --> 15:09.700
For what?

15:14.121 --> 15:16.165
[laughing]

15:24.048 --> 15:26.216
Now I know it's getting late,

15:26.300 --> 15:28.594
but we have one last order of business.

15:28.677 --> 15:32.181
Please welcome Newton High School senior
Paige Hardaway.

15:35.434 --> 15:36.769
♪ Dream bigger ♪

15:42.816 --> 15:43.776
♪ Dream... ♪

15:43.859 --> 15:44.693
[Woman] Ah.

15:44.777 --> 15:48.072
Whew! That was disorienting, wasn't it?

15:49.365 --> 15:52.201
Well, for my boyfriend Sam,

15:52.284 --> 15:55.329
life is always like that all the time.

15:56.038 --> 15:57.164
Um...

15:58.415 --> 16:00.751
You see, Sam has autism,

16:00.834 --> 16:04.380
which makes it really difficult
for him to deal with situations

16:04.463 --> 16:07.925
where there's large groups
of people and loud noises

16:08.008 --> 16:09.677
and unpredictable lighting.

16:09.760 --> 16:12.638
But should that mean that Sam is excluded

16:12.721 --> 16:14.181
from really fun things,

16:14.264 --> 16:16.934
like high school dances
that his girlfriend also

16:17.017 --> 16:19.269
really, really, really wants to go to?

16:19.353 --> 16:20.980
No. It doesn't.

16:21.480 --> 16:23.691
So, ladies and gentlemen,

16:23.774 --> 16:27.111
I present to you Silent Night,

16:27.194 --> 16:31.240
an autism-friendly dance
that is 100% silent.

16:31.323 --> 16:33.242
Let me guess, this is all your idea.

16:33.325 --> 16:35.035
No, I don't know anything about it.

16:35.119 --> 16:37.705
I didn't know Sam was interested
in going to the dance.

16:37.788 --> 16:42.209
And I already know what you're thinking.
I mean, silent? That's crazy.

16:42.918 --> 16:46.422
What about the music, right?
Well, there is gonna be music.

16:46.505 --> 16:49.008
It will be piped in
through wireless headphones.

16:49.091 --> 16:51.593
And I've already spoken
to the people at Techtropolis,

16:51.677 --> 16:54.304
and they are willing to donate headphones
for this event,

16:54.388 --> 16:55.931
which is super-cool of them.

16:57.057 --> 16:59.560
So in conclusion,

16:59.643 --> 17:01.729
I think that Newton High should be a place

17:01.812 --> 17:04.356
that's inclusive of all students.

17:06.608 --> 17:08.235
That's it. Thank you.

17:11.071 --> 17:13.240
Okay, so if we're ready to vote?

17:13.323 --> 17:14.783
Yes, April.

17:16.243 --> 17:17.077
Hi.

17:17.161 --> 17:18.245
[clears throat]

17:18.328 --> 17:21.915
I made JJ an appointment, months ago,
to get her hair done.

17:21.999 --> 17:23.917
It's going to cost me about $80.

17:24.585 --> 17:25.419
Um...

17:25.502 --> 17:29.715
Now you want to flatten it
with a bulky set of headphones.

17:29.798 --> 17:32.384
I... I think maybe no.

17:32.468 --> 17:35.387
Um, you know what?
Um, I'm a hairdresser.

17:35.471 --> 17:39.558
So I could do all the kids' hairdos
for free, you know.

17:39.641 --> 17:42.352
-Oh, wow, that would be wonderful, yes.
-Wow!

17:42.436 --> 17:44.563
[April] It's not just about
the hair, right?

17:45.230 --> 17:46.982
I mean, the Winter Formal

17:47.066 --> 17:49.443
is something that our kids
have looked forward to

17:49.526 --> 17:52.571
their entire high school career.

17:53.155 --> 17:56.450
Do we really need to change everything
to accommodate one kid?

17:57.242 --> 17:59.578
I mean, a silent dance, it's just so...

18:00.537 --> 18:01.914
you know, it's sad.

18:04.792 --> 18:06.293
[stammers]

18:06.376 --> 18:07.336
[clears throat]

18:07.419 --> 18:08.879
Well, maybe we should vote.

18:08.962 --> 18:10.297
You know what's sad?

18:11.381 --> 18:15.803
My son never being able
to attend a school event,

18:15.886 --> 18:18.555
because the sounds
are so overwhelming.

18:18.639 --> 18:21.141
You know, never being invited
to a birthday party,

18:21.225 --> 18:23.977
because he was the kid
at Chuck E. Cheese

18:24.061 --> 18:26.105
who couldn't stop screaming.

18:26.188 --> 18:29.441
The isolation, the loneliness,

18:30.609 --> 18:33.278
the lack of experience...

18:35.531 --> 18:36.782
that's sad.

18:38.033 --> 18:40.911
Your perfectly healthy kids
not being able to get an updo,

18:40.994 --> 18:43.038
it's just not on my list.

18:43.872 --> 18:44.706
So...

18:47.543 --> 18:49.670
Okay. Shall we vote?

18:50.337 --> 18:51.380
All the ayes?

18:53.632 --> 18:55.259
And the nays?

18:56.593 --> 18:58.303
Well, the ayes have it.

18:58.387 --> 19:01.723
-Silent dance, here we come.
-Yay!

19:01.807 --> 19:04.560
That's it, everybody. Thank you.
Meeting's adjourned.

19:04.643 --> 19:05.644
[laughs]

19:07.146 --> 19:08.438
[Paige] I'm so excited!

19:10.107 --> 19:11.024
Hey, April.

19:11.692 --> 19:14.486
Um, I'm just curious why you voted

19:14.570 --> 19:16.363
against the silent dance?

19:17.531 --> 19:20.242
Because the world
doesn't revolve around you.

19:20.325 --> 19:21.952
-I'm sorry?
-You should be.

19:22.035 --> 19:24.663
Oh, and I'm sure Casey's gonna love it
at Clayton Prep.

19:24.746 --> 19:27.791
Never mind what happens
to our girls' chances at a state title.

19:27.875 --> 19:32.171
-What does she have to do with this...
-Casey is the anchor in our relay.

19:32.254 --> 19:34.464
There's no way our girls
are gonna qualify without her.

19:34.548 --> 19:38.093
But who cares about that? Right?

19:44.224 --> 19:47.477
[cellphone vibrates]

19:49.271 --> 19:51.356
Case, hey, hon. You okay?

19:51.440 --> 19:53.734
We put our customers first,
so I'm going to help you out.

19:53.817 --> 19:56.195
I'm not ready to take
the D-Train to Bonetown.

19:56.278 --> 19:59.531
Sir, I got to handle this. Any other nerd
in a blue shirt can help you.

20:01.200 --> 20:02.367
What's up?

20:02.451 --> 20:04.578
How can I have sex
when I've never even seen boobs?

20:04.703 --> 20:06.872
Oh, is that what's going on?

20:06.955 --> 20:10.292
Look, when I was a kid,
I was terrified of the water.

20:10.375 --> 20:13.712
Then my dad decided it was time
for me to learn to swim,

20:13.795 --> 20:16.256
so he threw me in the deep end
at Holiday Inn.

20:16.340 --> 20:19.176
Now I swim like an otter.
You probably know all about those, huh?

20:19.259 --> 20:21.637
Of course. They can stay underwater
for up to four minutes,

20:21.720 --> 20:24.181
but what does swimming
have to do with sex?

20:35.067 --> 20:36.401
This isn't a swimming pool.

20:36.985 --> 20:38.737
Nope. It's a titty club.

20:38.820 --> 20:40.572
This way, you'll know what to expect

20:40.656 --> 20:42.991
and won't lose your shit
when you see Paige's boobs.

20:43.075 --> 20:45.535
And bonus, my cousin Sunil
caters the buffet here

20:45.619 --> 20:48.372
and it is off the chain!

20:48.455 --> 20:50.082
This guy knows what I'm talking 'bout.

20:52.417 --> 20:53.377
Okay.

20:54.002 --> 20:54.920
You ready for this?

20:57.172 --> 20:58.090
Yes.

21:20.654 --> 21:22.531
Nope! Not doing that.

21:22.614 --> 21:24.783
Too many lights, too much sound. No way.

21:24.866 --> 21:26.827
Okay, maybe that was a bad idea.

21:27.619 --> 21:30.247
Come to think of it,
I still have a recurring nightmare

21:30.330 --> 21:32.499
