shaped like my dad.

21:32.958 --> 21:34.835
You think that's connected?

21:34.918 --> 21:36.795
Hey, man. It's okay.

21:36.878 --> 21:38.130
You did good.

21:39.298 --> 21:42.301
But I was kind of looking forward
to the goat curry tacos.

21:42.384 --> 21:44.761
Have your tacos. I'll wait out here.

21:44.845 --> 21:46.638
I'll be quick. I won't get a lap dance.

21:46.722 --> 21:48.515
Just one plate, then we're out of here.
Cool?

21:48.974 --> 21:49.975
[snaps fingers]

21:54.438 --> 21:55.856
[Destiny] I get it, kid.

21:56.857 --> 21:59.693
I work here and this place
can be too much for me, too.

21:59.776 --> 22:01.278
I use earplugs.

22:01.778 --> 22:05.532
Earplugs can actually cause tinnitus,
which is a ringing in the ears.

22:05.615 --> 22:09.494
I use noise-canceling headphones.
They're much better. You should try them.

22:10.203 --> 22:11.913
-I'm Destiny.
-I'm Sam Gardner.

22:12.873 --> 22:15.542
So why are you standing out here
all alone, Sam Gardner?

22:16.585 --> 22:18.170
My girlfriend wants to have sex,

22:18.253 --> 22:20.047
but I'm nervous and ill-prepared.

22:20.130 --> 22:21.798
I've never even seen boobs before.

22:23.091 --> 22:25.594
-Want some advice?
-Yes, please.

22:27.804 --> 22:31.016
Just be kind to her.
That's all that really matters.

22:31.850 --> 22:33.435
Don't worry about the sex stuff.

22:33.518 --> 22:35.979
At a certain point,
biology will just take over.

22:36.563 --> 22:38.190
Biology is my favorite subject.

22:38.273 --> 22:39.566
Good for you.

22:40.817 --> 22:44.154
But just so that you'll feel
a little more prepared.

22:51.828 --> 22:52.829
Oh.

22:53.622 --> 22:54.456
Wow.

22:55.123 --> 22:56.875
Yeah. I know.

22:58.376 --> 22:59.961
Good luck with your girlfriend.

23:02.422 --> 23:03.757
'Sup, Destiny?

23:03.840 --> 23:05.050
Hey, Zahid.

23:06.718 --> 23:08.011
What did I miss?

23:15.018 --> 23:16.770
I got a fraud alert on my credit card.

23:16.853 --> 23:19.147
You have to pick the most
expensive dress in the store?

23:20.190 --> 23:21.399
[sobs]

23:21.483 --> 23:22.984
Oh, honey.

23:23.068 --> 23:25.821
I'm joking. I'm just kidding you.

23:30.659 --> 23:32.369
I don't want to go to Clayton Prep.

23:33.537 --> 23:34.496
Okay.

23:35.497 --> 23:37.332
And honestly...

23:39.376 --> 23:41.169
I don't know if I can go.

23:42.212 --> 23:45.006
Apparently they found out
that I punched Bailey Bennett.

23:45.090 --> 23:47.843
-I know. I check in with them.
-Then why are you telling people

23:47.926 --> 23:50.053
that I'm going to go there
and buying me shirts?

23:50.137 --> 23:51.847
Because I think you're amazing,

23:51.930 --> 23:53.765
and I think you're gonna get in anyway.

23:54.975 --> 23:56.059
I'm just...

23:56.143 --> 23:57.227
I'm...

23:58.562 --> 24:01.106
I'm scared because I don't want
to leave you guys

24:01.189 --> 24:04.359
and Evan and my team.

24:04.943 --> 24:08.655
Just the whole Clayton Prep thing
is starting to feel kind of like...

24:09.823 --> 24:10.866
Selfish.

24:10.949 --> 24:12.450
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

24:12.534 --> 24:14.202
Even Sharice turned against me.

24:14.286 --> 24:16.163
No. Sharice is your best friend.

24:16.246 --> 24:18.915
When you were little,
she followed you like a puppy dog.

24:18.999 --> 24:20.917
No, she was the one that stole my clothes.

24:21.001 --> 24:22.460
She's a little bitch.

24:22.544 --> 24:23.461
[laughs] I know.

24:28.091 --> 24:29.176
Honey...

24:29.926 --> 24:32.095
It's okay to be a little selfish.

24:36.308 --> 24:37.767
Thanks, Mom.

24:39.060 --> 24:40.312
You kept the tags on, right?

24:40.395 --> 24:41.479
Duh.

24:48.111 --> 24:49.112
How's your foot?

24:49.779 --> 24:53.033
They have to do an x-ray to make sure,
but they think it's fractured.

24:53.116 --> 24:54.075
I'm such an idiot.

24:54.159 --> 24:55.911
I'm sure I've seen way more idiotic.

24:55.994 --> 24:57.120
[laughs]

24:57.996 --> 24:59.915
Yeah, well, thanks for making me come.

24:59.998 --> 25:02.125
I would've ignored this forever
if it weren't for you.

25:02.209 --> 25:06.087
No problem. And I wanted to apologize
about asking you about my own stuff.

25:07.088 --> 25:10.926
I know you're Sam's therapist,
and you try to keep things professional.

25:11.635 --> 25:13.845
-Yeah.
-All right. I'll see you later.

25:15.931 --> 25:16.932
My brother's...

25:18.099 --> 25:19.893
My brother is autistic.

25:21.228 --> 25:24.648
Jesse. He's not as
high functioning as Sam.

25:24.731 --> 25:26.149
He's minimally verbal.

25:26.733 --> 25:29.361
As a kid, we couldn't even walk
through a parking lot

25:29.444 --> 25:33.156
because he'd have to stop behind every car
and read the license plate.

25:34.074 --> 25:36.660
But my parents didn't acknowledge

25:36.743 --> 25:39.371
he was on the spectrum till he was 16.

25:39.454 --> 25:40.413
Hmm.

25:40.497 --> 25:42.457
They kept insisting it was a speech issue

25:42.540 --> 25:43.959
and that he'd grow out of it.

25:45.877 --> 25:47.879
The saddest thing in my life

25:47.963 --> 25:51.424
is wondering what he would've been like
had he gotten interventions early.

25:52.175 --> 25:54.970
It's why I do what I do.

25:55.929 --> 25:59.057
They didn't want to acknowledge it
because they were ashamed.

25:59.140 --> 26:01.643
They were afraid of the social isolation

26:01.726 --> 26:03.520
that comes
with having a kid who's different.

26:04.896 --> 26:06.815
And I feel for them.

26:07.440 --> 26:09.484
You just want to pretend nothing's wrong.

26:10.944 --> 26:13.321
Yeah, well,
I used to be really good at that.

26:16.074 --> 26:18.243
All right, I should get going.

26:18.326 --> 26:22.622
And I'm gonna take you up
on that referral, if it's still okay.

26:23.290 --> 26:24.791
Yeah. Totally cool.

26:24.874 --> 26:26.126
-All right.
-I'll e-mail you.

26:26.209 --> 26:28.420
-Okay. Take it easy.
-Thanks.

26:31.673 --> 26:33.174
[cellphone rings]

26:36.219 --> 26:37.762
Hey. You need something?

26:38.513 --> 26:40.098
Um, no, I just...

26:41.182 --> 26:43.184
I just wanted to apologize.

26:44.769 --> 26:45.603
What?

26:45.687 --> 26:49.608
The way I handled the thing with Chuck
and not telling him about Sam.

26:51.735 --> 26:53.278
I don't know. I don't know.

26:53.361 --> 26:54.946
There's a part of me that's...

26:56.448 --> 26:58.074
that's ashamed.

26:58.783 --> 27:01.703
It's not who I am anymore,

27:01.786 --> 27:03.955
and it's not who I want to be anymore.

27:05.290 --> 27:06.791
Oh, honey.

27:06.875 --> 27:10.754
I don't know why, but I'm going to try
to continue to figure it out

27:10.837 --> 27:12.505
and deal with it better and...

27:12.589 --> 27:13.840
I just--

27:15.133 --> 27:16.676
I'm sorry, okay?

27:17.677 --> 27:18.720
I know.

27:19.929 --> 27:20.805
All right.

27:20.889 --> 27:23.183
Um, are you home yet?

27:23.266 --> 27:25.101
No. I just have, um...

27:25.935 --> 27:28.855
I have one little thing to do
and then I'll be home soon.

27:28.938 --> 27:31.775
Okay, well, I'll see you soon,
and I love you, okay?

27:33.318 --> 27:34.361
Bye.

27:39.491 --> 27:40.700
[Sharice] Mrs. Gardner?

27:41.659 --> 27:44.496
I really need to get to youth group.

27:44.579 --> 27:46.164
Yeah, I don't think so, Sharice.

27:47.123 --> 27:48.083
Where are we going?

27:49.209 --> 27:53.296
I've known you since the third grade.
I've hand-washed your retainer.

27:54.172 --> 27:56.758
I keep mint-flavored Oreos
at the house for you.

27:57.509 --> 28:00.720
Now I want to know what's going on,
and I want to know now.

28:04.474 --> 28:06.142
Okay, I know.

28:06.226 --> 28:08.144
I messed up, and I'm so sorry.

28:09.521 --> 28:11.272
Casey's my best friend, and...

28:11.356 --> 28:12.857
When I heard you were leaving

28:13.608 --> 28:16.111
I just got upset.
I can't believe you didn't tell me.

28:16.945 --> 28:20.073
Well, I didn't want to jinx it.
And I'm not even in the school yet.

28:20.156 --> 28:22.075
You don't tell me anything anymore.

28:22.158 --> 28:24.869
You've got a boyfriend,
and I never see you,

28:24.953 --> 28:27.956
and you got your hair cut
without even talking to me about it.

28:28.039 --> 28:29.249
Okay.

28:30.041 --> 28:31.042
Okay.

28:32.043 --> 28:34.129
-I'm sorry.
-Me, too.

28:34.879 --> 28:36.047
Come here.

28:37.632 --> 28:39.092
Oh! [laughs]

28:40.135 --> 28:42.804
Sharice, this is dumb.

28:43.555 --> 28:45.765
But do you want to be my date
to the dance?

28:46.683 --> 28:50.520
Are you only asking me
'cause Evan can't go because he's a thief?

28:50.603 --> 28:51.604
Yes.

28:51.688 --> 28:53.273
I'd love to!

28:53.356 --> 28:54.691
Okay, great. [laughs]

28:54.774 --> 28:55.734
Come on.

28:57.819 --> 28:59.362
Yuck. Your feet stink.

29:00.071 --> 29:01.322
What are you drawing?

29:02.532 --> 29:04.909
A portrait of a wise woman I met today.

29:04.993 --> 29:07.579
Oh, my God! Try to unsee!
Try to unsee!

29:07.662 --> 29:09.622
I'm familiarizing myself
with the female body

29:09.706 --> 29:13.376
-in anticipation of losing my virginity.
-Try to unhear! Try to unhear!

29:13.460 --> 29:15.336
-Oh, my God, Sam!
-What?

29:15.420 --> 29:17.422
That's disgusting!
You need to put that away!

29:17.505 --> 29:19.340
-Seriously, don't--
-I'm not putting it away.

29:19.424 --> 29:21.384
-Erase it. Who taught you that?
-It's beautiful.

29:21.468 --> 29:23.470
-What was that? Ew!
-Destiny taught me that.

29:23.553 --> 29:25.388
[Casey] Are you watching porn online?

29:25.472 --> 29:27.307
-Sam, that's a serious problem.
-I'm not.

29:27.390 --> 29:30.435
-[Sam] I went to a strip bar.
-[chattering continues]

29:30.518 --> 29:33.062
[Sam] I met Destiny, and she's very nice.

29:33.146 --> 29:34.647
She was very nice.

29:39.652 --> 29:40.570
Finally.

29:40.653 --> 29:43.865
My phone died an hour ago.
I've been sitting alone with my thoughts.

29:43.948 --> 29:46.868
And I'm in the middle of a breakup,
so that is not a fun place to be.

29:46.951 --> 29:49.245
Well, we won't be
performing an x-ray today.

29:49.954 --> 29:52.123
Why not? My ankle's okay?

29:52.999 --> 29:55.376
Miss Sasaki,
are you aware you're pregnant?

29:57.212 --> 29:59.881
[rock music plays]

30:04.594 --> 30:07.806
♪ Don't look ahead
There's stormy weather ♪

30:10.892 --> 30:13.686
♪ Another roadblock in our way ♪

30:17.190 --> 30:20.360
♪ But if we go, we go together ♪

30:23.530 --> 30:26.491
♪ Our hands are tied here if we stay ♪

30:28.076 --> 30:31.496
♪ Oh, we set our dreams to carry us ♪

30:31.579 --> 30:34.499
♪ If they don't come we will run ♪

30:34.582 --> 30:37.794
♪ Now we push right past to find out ♪

30:37.877 --> 30:40.672
